---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Home" active="home">
  <div class="hero">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="kicker">Extended English</p>
      <h1>Macbeth, studied properly.</h1>
      <p class="lede" style="max-width:36em;">Scene-by-scene guides to the play, the characters and their arcs, key quotations, and clear guidance on the Shakespeare coursework assignment. This site is growing: the framework is here, and the guides arrive as the unit is taught.</p>
      <p style="margin-top: 1.6rem;">
        <a class="pill" href="/guide/" style="font-size: 0.85rem; padding: 0.5rem 1.2rem; text-decoration: none;">What&rsquo;s coming →</a>
        <a class="pill" href="/coursework/" style="font-size: 0.85rem; padding: 0.5rem 1.2rem; text-decoration: none;">The coursework, explained →</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="band">
    <div class="wrap prose">
      <h2 style="margin-top:0;">What this site will hold</h2>
      <ul class="tick">
        <li>Act-by-act, scene-by-scene guides with staging and language analysis</li>
        <li>Character studies: the Macbeths, Banquo, Duncan, Macduff, the Witches</li>
        <li>A quotation bank with act, scene and line references</li>
        <li>Context that earns its place: kingship, the supernatural, James I</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="small">Part of the Extended English family, alongside the Klara and the Sun, Kindertransport and Poetry Anthology guides.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
